cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.PL

The paper deals with the decidability of a subclass of weighted timed games, which involves both logic and game theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computation of optimal values, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of automata and the analysis of their properties suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the decidability of untimed games, which could be related to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the decision problem, which could be related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
